This is an action RPG boss battle. Avoid the enemy's attacks
and attack with the A key. While holding the D key, you can
move while keeping your direction fixed.

If either your stamina or health reaches zero from the
enemy's attacks, you will be defeated. Generally, ranged
attacks will decrease health, and contact will decrease
stamina.

When you come into contact with the enemy, you'll be held
and continue to take damage until you succeed at the timing
bar. Let's try out the timing bar.

Stopping on yellow is a success, stopping on red is a
critical. If you stop on yellow, you'll take damage and be
released, while stopping on red will halve the damage and
release you.

Furthermore, taking damage to your stamina from the enemy
will put you in a [Color_14]state of arousal\C[0], which
reduces the number of slashes during your attacks. A heart
mark will appear on your status during arousal.

Arousal can be removed by walking around a set number of
steps. It will also be removed if you shake off the enemy
with a critical. If possible, aim to stop on red.

Learn the enemy's attack patterns. The enemy's attacks have
patterns. Focus on dodging first to memorize them.

Make use of the D key's direction lock. Locking your
direction makes it easier to attack and evade. Attacking
while retreating can make the battle easier.

Use healing items and skills. There are no usage
restrictions for healing items and skills (like deep
breathing). You can heal and push through aggressively if
needed.

will significantly lower the difficulty level. There are no
downsides to this.
